17/02/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Lia Roberts, chief of the Republican Party in the US state of Nevada, announced on Monday (16 February) that she would run in Romania's November presidential election. 
Roberts left Romania in 1979 after marrying an American. 
She is promising to eliminate corruption and streamline the government. 
She plans to run as an independent candidate and spend several million dollars on her campaign. 
(Reuters, AFP - 16/02/04)
